name: Simone Biles
summary: Simone Biles, the decorated gymnast, has made headlines during the 2024 Paris Olympics. Despite skipping the Opening Ceremony, Biles has had a significant impact on American society, as discussed in a Washington Post opinion piece. She has overcome a calf injury to perform exceptionally well in Olympic gymnastics qualifying, impressing observers with her perseverance. Biles's return to the Olympics has been met with praise, with experts noting her ability to defy age expectations. Remarkably, she even attempted her signature "Biles II" vault in practice, further showcasing her extraordinary talent. Biles's performance at the Olympics has drawn attention from celebrities like Snoop Dogg, who witnessed her impressive performance firsthand. Despite challenges, Biles continues to push boundaries and inspire others with her determination and resilience.

name: Venezuela
summary: Venezuela's political landscape is at a crossroads as it approaches a pivotal presidential election. The opposition, seeking to end the socialist government's 25-year rule, faces off against incumbent Nicolás Maduro. This election holds high stakes, with the potential to either extend Maduro's power or establish a seismic political shift. Concerns have been raised over repression and irregularities surrounding the election, but Venezuelans eagerly await the results and the possibility of a change in their nation's governance. Meanwhile, many Venezuelans living abroad hope for a reversal of fortune that will allow them to eventually return home.

A Wall Street Journal poll showed that Kamala Harris has surpassed Trump in the race. TIME published an article about Donald Trump's niece alleging he advocated for the death of disabled individuals. The Associated Press reported on Trump's focus on Harris at his first rally since Biden's withdrawal. USA TODAY raised questions about the lack of discussion on gun control in the wake of the shooting. The House Committee on Oversight and Reform held a hearing investigating the Secret Service and the assassination attempt. CNN reported that the Trump campaign is hesitant to commit to a debate with Harris until her nomination is confirmed. NBC News confirmed that a bullet struck Trump's ear during the attempt.

name: Fantastic Four
summary: Marvel unveiled details about its upcoming "Fantastic Four" movie at Comic-Con. The official title of the film is "The Fantastic Four: First Steps," and it will feature a retro 1960s setting. Concept footage from the film showcased a glimpse of Galactus' head and hinted at a retro vision for the iconic superhero team. The cast, including Pedro Pascal as Mr. Fantastic, took to the stage to share their excitement for the project. Marvel also confirmed that the core four members of the Fantastic Four will appear in the next two "Avengers" movies, indicating their importance within the Marvel Cinematic Universe. Despite the "First Steps" title, the film's creative team emphasized that it is not an origin story but rather a unique take on the classic characters. The cast and crew expressed their enthusiasm for bringing the Fantastic Four to life on the big screen.

name: Nic Fink
summary: Dallas native Nic Fink, a unique figure in the world of swimming, has showcased a remarkable ability to balance his passion for the sport with a demanding 9-to-5 engineering job. This extraordinary achievement recently culminated in a silver medal at the 2024 Paris Olympics in the 100-meter breaststroke event. Fink's journey has drawn widespread attention, with the 2024 Olympic medalist becoming the oldest first-time U.S. Olympic swimmer to win a medal since 1904. His success has been a testament to his unwavering determination and the ability to strike a harmonious "swim-life balance." Despite the rigors of his dual existence, Fink has persevered, proving that it is possible to excel in both professional and athletic pursuits.

summary: A series of news articles have been released regarding an assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump. The Secret Service director admitted to lawmakers that "we failed" in their response to the assassination attempt. A new House task force has been formed to investigate the incident. The New York Times outlines what is known about the assassination attempt thus far. USA Today raises the issue of gun control in relation to the incident. A local SWAT team has blamed the assassination attempt on a lack of planning and communication. The FBI director has revealed that the gunman searched for information on the JFK assassination. Grassley released bodycam videos of the assassination attempt, and new video of the aftermath shows a body on a roof.
